1
00:00:01,347 --> 00:00:03,724
[theme music plays]

2
00:01:31,842 --> 00:01:35,804
I think we should do this every day.
The sun will do you good.

3
00:01:43,895 --> 00:01:45,606
What in the world

4
00:01:46,423 --> 00:01:49,818
am I supposed to do now?

5
00:01:51,862 --> 00:01:53,822
[wind howling]

6
00:01:54,573 --> 00:01:57,492
FATHER

7
00:02:04,374 --> 00:02:05,626
[groans]

8
00:02:12,007 --> 00:02:12,924
[Sidoh]
Hi, Ryuk.

9
00:02:17,686 --> 00:02:20,474
Sidoh, what are you doing here?

10
00:02:23,727 --> 00:02:26,188
Hey, quit following me.

11
00:02:28,857 --> 00:02:30,275
I want my notebook.

12
00:02:30,859 --> 00:02:33,195
Damn, guess I shouldn't be surprised.

13
00:02:33,779 --> 00:02:34,696
Too bad.

14
00:02:34,946 --> 00:02:37,532
Things got a little complicated recently.

15
00:02:37,658 --> 00:02:39,660
I have no idea where it is.

16
00:02:39,993 --> 00:02:41,620
Why am I not surprised?

17
00:02:45,540 --> 00:02:48,001
Look, I told you,
stop following me.

18
00:02:48,293 --> 00:02:49,878
Then give me back my notebook.

19
00:02:49,961 --> 00:02:51,546
[exasperated]
I don't know where it is.

20
00:02:53,799 --> 00:02:56,259
If you want it back, you're gonna have to
look for it yourself.

21
00:02:56,885 --> 00:02:59,096
Moron.
[continues munching apple loudly]

22
00:03:00,681 --> 00:03:03,517
[Shuichi Aizawa] Wammy's House
isn't exactly a normal orphanage.

23
00:03:04,226 --> 00:03:06,269
It's like a school
for gifted children.

24
00:03:06,395 --> 00:03:07,479
But here's the crazy part.

25
00:03:07,938 --> 00:03:12,192
Its real purpose is to groom these kids
so that one of them can become the next L.

26
00:03:13,068 --> 00:03:14,403
[Light Yagami] L's successor.

27
00:03:15,028 --> 00:03:17,656
[Aizawa] Apparently the one most likely
to succeed L

28
00:03:17,739 --> 00:03:19,157
is this kid named Near.

29
00:03:19,366 --> 00:03:21,201
[Light] Near. Is that N?

30
00:03:21,493 --> 00:03:24,955
Also, we founds some leads on Mello,
the one N mentioned.

31
00:03:25,163 --> 00:03:28,125
He's smart too,
but he always came second to Near.

32
00:03:28,333 --> 00:03:31,920
[Light] So Near was meant to be
L's successor. There's no mistake.

33
00:03:32,045 --> 00:03:33,255
He has to be N.

34
00:03:33,380 --> 00:03:35,090
He's the one commanding
the SPK.

35
00:03:35,549 --> 00:03:39,010
As for Mello, he would have wanted
to become L's successor.

36
00:03:39,136 --> 00:03:41,096
But he probably lost out to Near.

37
00:03:41,471 --> 00:03:42,556
That gives him a motive

38
00:03:42,639 --> 00:03:44,933
for wanting to get his hands on
the notebook first.

39
00:03:45,809 --> 00:03:47,561
It all adds up perfectly.

40
00:03:48,019 --> 00:03:51,356
This guy is definitely the same Mello
that N told us about.

41
00:03:52,065 --> 00:03:53,775
[Aizawa]
These are sketches of both of them.

42
00:03:54,443 --> 00:03:56,153
We couldn't find any photographs.

43
00:03:57,821 --> 00:03:59,573
[Light] L's successors.

44
00:04:00,323 --> 00:04:03,994
Looks like I'm still fighting L
after all this time.

45
00:04:07,038 --> 00:04:08,915
But first thing's first.
I have to find out

46
00:04:09,040 --> 00:04:11,501
where Mello and his mafia associates
are hiding themselves.

47
00:04:11,793 --> 00:04:14,337
I already had Misa check
a list of known Mafia syndicates

48
00:04:14,671 --> 00:04:16,339
using her Shinigami eyes.

49
00:04:17,758 --> 00:04:20,635
[Misa Amane gasps] Look, I found him.
I can't see his lifespan.

50
00:04:21,052 --> 00:04:24,264
He's number 105.
They have him listed as Jack Neylon.

51
00:04:24,639 --> 00:04:27,225
But his real name is Kal Snydar.
He's got the notebook.

52
00:04:27,517 --> 00:04:30,395
[Light] After that, it was the simple
matter of using the death note

53
00:04:30,479 --> 00:04:34,024
to make Snydar send a letter to me with
the location of the gang's hideout.

54
00:04:34,357 --> 00:04:35,776
It should be arriving soon.

55
00:04:36,234 --> 00:04:37,319
[door creaks]

56
00:04:37,819 --> 00:04:41,364
[gasps] Hi, Light.
Great news! The letter arrived.

57
00:04:42,824 --> 00:04:43,909
[Light]
He's in LA.

58
00:04:44,409 --> 00:04:47,913
I did it. I out-maneuvered
both Near and Mello.

59
00:04:48,038 --> 00:04:49,289
Guess it's no surprise.

60
00:04:49,372 --> 00:04:54,127
As long as I have the notebook
and Misa's eyes, I'm unstoppable.

61
00:04:57,714 --> 00:05:01,593
So, Light. I guess this means
I was helpful to you again, doesn't it?

62
00:05:02,135 --> 00:05:05,305
Yeah.
I love you, Misa.

63
00:05:07,432 --> 00:05:10,644
[Misa sighs, giggles]

64
00:05:12,020 --> 00:05:14,898
[Sidoh]
Los Angeles.

65
00:05:29,955 --> 00:05:31,915
The next step is for me to figure out

66
00:05:31,998 --> 00:05:34,417
just how much I can control people
with this thing.

67
00:05:34,918 --> 00:05:37,420
[Sidoh] Oh, they're gonna have to
be able to see me

68
00:05:37,587 --> 00:05:40,966
before I can even talk to them.
What a drag.

69
00:05:42,008 --> 00:05:44,719
Looks like Snydar is
the owner right now.

70
00:05:45,095 --> 00:05:48,014
Guess I'll have to make him
touch the notebook first.

71
00:05:48,890 --> 00:05:50,225
Oh, well...

72
00:05:51,601 --> 00:05:52,477
[gasps]

73
00:05:53,895 --> 00:05:55,063
[Sidoh] Tag, you're it.

74
00:05:55,605 --> 00:05:58,400
What the...
The notebook just flew.

75
00:05:59,526 --> 00:06:01,862
[chuckles]
It's a notebook that kills people.

76
00:06:02,070 --> 00:06:03,947
Hell,
nothing surprises me anymore.

77
00:06:04,155 --> 00:06:05,407
[screaming]

78
00:06:05,907 --> 00:06:07,117
[yelling]
Boss, who is this?

79
00:06:07,200 --> 00:06:09,870
The guy in the freaky costume,
who the hell is he?

80
00:06:09,953 --> 00:06:11,162
Who brought him here?

81
00:06:11,288 --> 00:06:14,207
I came here on my own.
I'm actually a Shinigami.

82
00:06:14,624 --> 00:06:17,669
[man] A Shinigami?
[laughs hysterically]

83
00:06:18,044 --> 00:06:20,422
If you don't want everyone to think
you're crazy,

84
00:06:20,589 --> 00:06:23,258
pass the notebook around
so they can see me, too.

85
00:06:23,758 --> 00:06:25,260
-[groans]
-[notebook slides on floor]

86
00:06:25,802 --> 00:06:27,846
He says you can see him
if you touch the notebook.

87
00:06:28,054 --> 00:06:30,140
[groans]
Please, everyone, touch it.

88
00:06:30,599 --> 00:06:32,183
I swear I'm not crazy.

89
00:06:34,436 --> 00:06:36,980
Fine. Whatever.
Come on, guys.

90
00:06:37,230 --> 00:06:39,065
Touch the notebook.

91
00:06:40,817 --> 00:06:43,987
[indistinct yelling]

92
00:06:46,489 --> 00:06:47,741
[bullet casings clink on floor]

93
00:06:49,409 --> 00:06:52,454
Nice try.
You humans can't kill a Shinigami.

94
00:06:52,913 --> 00:06:54,456
[gasping]

95
00:06:54,664 --> 00:06:56,917
Jack's right.
That ain't no costume.

96
00:06:57,250 --> 00:07:00,462
That's a real, live Shinigami.
So now what do we do?

97
00:07:01,803 --> 00:07:02,797
[Light] Ryuk.

98
00:07:03,465 --> 00:07:06,801
As of now, I'm going to forfeit ownership
of this notebook.

99
00:07:07,177 --> 00:07:11,306
All I ask is that you agree to follow
whichever person I give it to.

100
00:07:11,514 --> 00:07:13,892
[man] What?
You're giving up ownership again?

101
00:07:14,100 --> 00:07:17,103
[Misa] But wait. Won't you lose
all your memories if you do that?

102
00:07:17,437 --> 00:07:19,439
Misa, lend me your notebook.

103
00:07:20,565 --> 00:07:22,025
I'll keep it on me like this.

104
00:07:22,233 --> 00:07:24,527
That way, even if I forfeit ownership
of my notebook

105
00:07:24,653 --> 00:07:26,029
I won't lose my memory.

106
00:07:26,363 --> 00:07:27,948
I'll give you as many pages you need.

107
00:07:28,448 --> 00:07:29,407
From this moment on,

108
00:07:29,491 --> 00:07:31,660
you're going to be Kira.
Can you do that?

109
00:07:32,202 --> 00:07:35,789
Of course. But I don't get
why you're doing this.

110
00:07:36,456 --> 00:07:38,792
I'll explain everything to you right now.

111
00:07:39,459 --> 00:07:41,002
I won't forgive any mistakes.

112
00:07:43,505 --> 00:07:45,090
[loud munching]

113
00:07:45,799 --> 00:07:47,884
-Chocolate is so good.
-Hey.

114
00:07:48,009 --> 00:07:50,345
What about that stuff you told us?
Is it true?

115
00:07:51,054 --> 00:07:53,598
"If the person using the note
fails to consecutively write

116
00:07:53,723 --> 00:07:56,226
names of people to be killed
within 13 days of each other,

117
00:07:56,351 --> 00:07:57,686
then the user will die.

118
00:07:57,936 --> 00:08:00,981
If you make this note unusable
by tearing it up or burning it,

119
00:08:01,064 --> 00:08:03,692
all the humans who have touched
the note till then will die."

120
00:08:04,025 --> 00:08:06,528
Are you saying
those two rules were made up?

121
00:08:06,778 --> 00:08:10,323
[clears throat]
Oh yeah, those rules are definitely fake.

122
00:08:10,532 --> 00:08:13,284
My guess is some Shinigami wrote those
down as a joke

123
00:08:13,410 --> 00:08:15,286
before giving the notebook
to a human. [munches]

124
00:08:16,371 --> 00:08:20,583
[Mello] As for the 13-day rule, we can
test that out by using one of our people.

125
00:08:20,875 --> 00:08:22,168
But the real question is,

126
00:08:22,335 --> 00:08:25,255
was this the notebook
that was used by Kira?

127
00:08:25,588 --> 00:08:29,134
And if so, was he aware
that these two rules were false?

128
00:08:29,843 --> 00:08:33,346
If he did know, he could have used
these rules to his advantage.

129
00:08:33,763 --> 00:08:34,723
In particular,

130
00:08:34,806 --> 00:08:37,767
the 13-day rule would have allowed him
to prove his innocence

131
00:08:37,851 --> 00:08:39,519
in only 13 days.

132
00:08:40,395 --> 00:08:41,479
[keeps munching]

133
00:08:41,563 --> 00:08:45,025
-[Mello] Sidoh, go keep watch outside.
-Huh?

134
00:08:45,775 --> 00:08:48,820
It will be very convenient for us
that you can't be seen by humans.

135
00:08:49,154 --> 00:08:51,656
Go outside and keep watch. Got it?

136
00:08:52,449 --> 00:08:53,825
[Sidoh] What's with this guy?

137
00:08:53,950 --> 00:08:57,078
He's human,
but he's scary.

138
00:08:57,954 --> 00:08:59,080
[phone rings]

139
00:09:03,960 --> 00:09:04,836
Yagami speaking.

140
00:09:05,754 --> 00:09:07,005
This is Kira.

141
00:09:07,464 --> 00:09:09,674
-[Touta Matsuda] What did he say?
-[Soichiro Yagami] Kira?

142
00:09:09,841 --> 00:09:12,552
[Kira] I understand that the notebook
that was in your possession

143
00:09:12,635 --> 00:09:14,679
has fallen into criminal hands.

144
00:09:15,263 --> 00:09:18,516
[Yagami]
Can you prove that you are the real Kira?

145
00:09:18,725 --> 00:09:21,186
[Kira] Prove it? Now that there are others
using the notebook,

146
00:09:21,352 --> 00:09:24,397
there's no point in predicting killings
in order to identify myself.

147
00:09:24,522 --> 00:09:26,900
They could just as easily kill
the same targets.

148
00:09:27,484 --> 00:09:30,153
But don't worry,
I've already taken this into account.

149
00:09:30,278 --> 00:09:33,907
I've sent you something that will
clearly prove to you that I am Kira.

150
00:09:34,074 --> 00:09:35,867
It's my own notebook.

151
00:09:36,076 --> 00:09:37,410
[Yagami] Wha... What do you mean?

152
00:09:37,911 --> 00:09:39,204
[Kira]
The notebook I've sent you

153
00:09:39,287 --> 00:09:42,332
gives me the power to know
a person's name by only seeing their face,

154
00:09:42,415 --> 00:09:44,626
and you will be able to gain
that same power.

155
00:09:44,793 --> 00:09:45,919
Do you understand?

156
00:09:46,211 --> 00:09:47,796
[Misa] Please stay calm.

157
00:09:48,088 --> 00:09:50,298
and listen carefully.

158
00:09:51,216 --> 00:09:54,803
I've gathered information
from the FBI and other sources.

159
00:09:54,928 --> 00:09:58,598
On November 10th, at exactly 11:59 p.m.

160
00:09:58,723 --> 00:10:01,810
arrangements have been made
so that all known associates

161
00:10:01,893 --> 00:10:04,145
-of the mafia will die.
-[gasping]

162
00:10:05,688 --> 00:10:07,524
[Kira/Misa]
It's already written in my notebook.

163
00:10:07,649 --> 00:10:09,901
so it's impossible for me to make
any changes

164
00:10:10,026 --> 00:10:12,028
You will not be able
to prevent these deaths.

165
00:10:12,195 --> 00:10:13,613
I already know their location.

166
00:10:13,822 --> 00:10:16,241
I will hand over that information
along with the notebook,

167
00:10:16,491 --> 00:10:17,367
so remember...

168
00:10:17,867 --> 00:10:22,330
on November 10th, 11:59 p.m.,
that's when it all happens.

169
00:10:22,497 --> 00:10:25,917
That moment is your best
and only chance to get the notebook back.

170
00:10:26,084 --> 00:10:27,293
It's up to you.

171
00:10:27,752 --> 00:10:28,837
[gasps softly]

172
00:10:52,902 --> 00:10:54,028
[Light] What should we do?

173
00:10:54,154 --> 00:10:57,657
If the Mafia members are going to die
on the day Kira specified,

174
00:10:57,740 --> 00:10:59,659
it would be a chance to get
the notebook back.

175
00:10:59,784 --> 00:11:02,871
I don't like the idea of following
Kira's plan, but it's our best option.

176
00:11:02,996 --> 00:11:04,164
[Ryuk]
Exactly.

177
00:11:06,374 --> 00:11:07,667
[Ryuk grunts]

178
00:11:09,919 --> 00:11:10,962
But still,

179
00:11:11,212 --> 00:11:12,922
knowing the time of death
for these guys

180
00:11:13,047 --> 00:11:15,133
isn't going to be enough for us
to make our move.

181
00:11:15,758 --> 00:11:18,595
[stammers] Ide, I think we both know
what needs to be done.

182
00:11:18,887 --> 00:11:20,597
We get the Shinigami
to follow us in,

183
00:11:20,805 --> 00:11:24,726
and then we do the deal for the eyes
and make sure they're all dead, right?

184
00:11:26,728 --> 00:11:28,313
I will make the deal for the eyes.

185
00:11:29,439 --> 00:11:32,275
[excitedly] No way, chief.
Let me be the one to do it.

186
00:11:32,442 --> 00:11:36,070
I was responsible for handing over
the notebook in the first place.

187
00:11:36,321 --> 00:11:39,449
Since that moment, I've been unable
to live with what I've done.

188
00:11:39,574 --> 00:11:41,284
I've even thought of killing myself.

189
00:11:41,409 --> 00:11:44,579
I'll use the notebook
to kill any criminals who try to stop us.

190
00:11:44,871 --> 00:11:48,499
And after 13 days, I'll die as well.

191
00:11:50,001 --> 00:11:52,086
[Light]
If Dad writes a name in the notebook,

192
00:11:52,629 --> 00:11:55,173
then...
when the time comes...

193
00:11:57,756 --> 00:12:01,638
NOVEMBER 10, 23:47

194
00:12:05,600 --> 00:12:08,353
Report,
is everybody ready to move in?

195
00:12:08,519 --> 00:12:09,395
[all] Roger.

196
00:12:10,146 --> 00:12:12,565
All right. Deputy Director,

197
00:12:13,566 --> 00:12:16,653
make the eye deal
with the Shinigami.

198
00:12:19,697 --> 00:12:21,658
All right, Ryuk. I'm ready.

199
00:12:22,659 --> 00:12:23,952
Sure thing, boss.

200
00:12:26,746 --> 00:12:28,539
[loud rumbling]

201
00:12:29,582 --> 00:12:31,626
[high pitched noise rings out]

202
00:12:35,505 --> 00:12:38,508
Once you're finished,
I want you to look at the photographs

203
00:12:38,633 --> 00:12:39,801
of the criminals I gave you.

204
00:12:39,884 --> 00:12:41,970
Can you see their names and life spans?

205
00:12:42,679 --> 00:12:44,138
[Yagami]
Yes, I can.

206
00:12:45,014 --> 00:12:47,642
Their name should disappear soon.
That's your cue.

207
00:13:00,071 --> 00:13:01,948
[clock ticking]

208
00:13:08,538 --> 00:13:09,831
[screaming]

209
00:13:10,957 --> 00:13:12,208
Everyone, move in!

210
00:13:26,055 --> 00:13:28,349
[Mello] So, Kira's involved
after all.

211
00:13:29,267 --> 00:13:30,852
I didn't think he'd go this far.

212
00:13:31,269 --> 00:13:33,021
My plan was supposed to be perfect.

213
00:13:33,521 --> 00:13:35,648
Damn. What the hell is Sidoh doing?

214
00:13:36,649 --> 00:13:39,235
Relax, Sidoh.
Just shut up and watch, all right?

215
00:13:39,652 --> 00:13:41,738
All you have to do is sit here
and do nothing.

216
00:13:41,904 --> 00:13:44,157
If you can do that,
you'll get your notebook back.

217
00:13:48,161 --> 00:13:49,412
Roy. Skyer.

218
00:13:49,579 --> 00:13:51,122
The notebook is under Rod's body

219
00:13:51,331 --> 00:13:53,166
Bring it to
the surveillance room upstairs.

220
00:13:57,920 --> 00:13:59,464
[groaning]

221
00:14:02,759 --> 00:14:03,885
[coughing]

222
00:14:05,053 --> 00:14:06,137
[Aizawa yells] Don't move.

223
00:14:13,644 --> 00:14:16,022
[Yagami] L, we've apprehended two
of the criminals .

224
00:14:16,314 --> 00:14:18,316
We've also been able to secure
the notebook.

225
00:14:18,941 --> 00:14:20,401
[Aizawa]
We'll being withdrawing now.

226
00:14:21,027 --> 00:14:22,820
Not yet. Keep going.

227
00:14:23,196 --> 00:14:24,447
-Huh?
-[man] What?

228
00:14:25,198 --> 00:14:28,159
[Light] We still haven't found anyone
who resembles our picture of Mello.

229
00:14:28,534 --> 00:14:30,745
That means he must be hiding
somewhere in the building.

230
00:14:31,913 --> 00:14:33,247
We've come this far.

231
00:14:33,373 --> 00:14:35,541
Let's finish this.
Do a thorough search.

232
00:14:50,731 --> 00:14:51,629
[men scream]

233
00:14:51,729 --> 00:14:53,559
-[Matsuda] What's was that?
-[Aizawa] An explosion?

234
00:14:54,894 --> 00:14:55,937
[Mello] Don't move.

235
00:14:56,270 --> 00:14:58,981
I've already blown up the two entrances
to this place.

236
00:14:59,273 --> 00:15:00,983
This will be your only warning.

237
00:15:01,150 --> 00:15:03,319
The next explosion will take out
the entire building

238
00:15:03,403 --> 00:15:04,946
as well as all your men inside.

239
00:15:05,655 --> 00:15:07,490
So you better do as I say.

240
00:15:08,282 --> 00:15:09,909
[Light]
It's Mello.

241
00:15:13,162 --> 00:15:14,872
-[Mello chuckles]
-[Yagami] Hm?

242
00:15:15,373 --> 00:15:16,666
Yagami again, huh?

243
00:15:17,583 --> 00:15:19,919
Maybe I should have killed you
when I had the chance.

244
00:15:20,002 --> 00:15:21,546
History repeats itself.

245
00:15:21,921 --> 00:15:24,215
But I never dreamed in a million years,

246
00:15:24,298 --> 00:15:26,592
that I'd be bargaining for the notebook
with you again.

247
00:15:27,552 --> 00:15:29,137
[high pitched noise rings out]

248
00:15:29,387 --> 00:15:35,059
[Yagami]
M-I-H-A-E-L K-E-E-H-L.

249
00:15:36,185 --> 00:15:39,397
Your real name is Mihael Keehl.

250
00:15:39,689 --> 00:15:41,941
[Mello]
What the hell...? How did he...?

251
00:15:42,358 --> 00:15:43,234
I did it.

252
00:15:43,609 --> 00:15:46,028
It's over, Mello.
It's time to turn yourself in.

253
00:15:46,320 --> 00:15:49,490
If you give up, I won't kill you.
You have my word on that.

254
00:15:50,324 --> 00:15:52,618
[Light]
What are you doing? Don't be stupid!

255
00:15:52,743 --> 00:15:54,328
Write his name down and kill him!
Now!

256
00:15:56,164 --> 00:15:59,667
You know how this works.
I write your name and you will die.

257
00:16:00,251 --> 00:16:03,045
Let go of that trigger
and put your hands in the air.

258
00:16:11,596 --> 00:16:13,222
-[Mello] Yagami...
-Don't move!

259
00:16:13,639 --> 00:16:14,849
I've written your first name

260
00:16:14,932 --> 00:16:17,185
and it will only take me a second
to write your surname.

261
00:16:18,019 --> 00:16:20,563
[Light grumbles]
You idiot! Just write it! Kill him!

262
00:16:20,980 --> 00:16:22,315
I'm truly sorry.

263
00:16:23,024 --> 00:16:26,402
For what it's worth, I give you my word
that I never wanted to kill you.

264
00:16:32,116 --> 00:16:33,659
But tell me, Yagami.

265
00:16:34,702 --> 00:16:36,537
You've never killed someone before,
have you?

266
00:16:40,750 --> 00:16:41,834
[grunting]

267
00:16:43,503 --> 00:16:44,670
Fire?

268
00:16:45,963 --> 00:16:47,256
[bullet casings clink on floor]

269
00:16:47,507 --> 00:16:48,841
[groaning]

270
00:16:52,094 --> 00:16:53,095
[man]
What was that?

271
00:16:53,763 --> 00:16:55,014
Jose! The notebook!

272
00:16:55,431 --> 00:16:56,849
[Jose] Damn!

273
00:16:57,266 --> 00:16:59,602
This guy.
He won't let go of the thing.

274
00:17:00,144 --> 00:17:02,313
Son of a... [strains]

275
00:17:02,522 --> 00:17:04,315
-[footsteps]
-Huh?

276
00:17:05,608 --> 00:17:06,734
[gasping]

277
00:17:14,242 --> 00:17:15,326
[Mello] Deputy Director!

278
00:17:18,454 --> 00:17:19,789
[Aizawa]
It's all over, Mello.

279
00:17:20,122 --> 00:17:21,624
Put your hands up and surrender.

280
00:17:31,342 --> 00:17:32,260
[gasping]

281
00:17:43,688 --> 00:17:45,439
[Aizawa] Matsuda, are you all right?

282
00:17:45,898 --> 00:17:47,525
[Matsuda] No, I don't think so.

283
00:17:47,858 --> 00:17:49,193
[Yagami] I'm sure you'll live.

284
00:17:49,527 --> 00:17:51,779
[Aizawa] L, I don't see any sign of Mello.

285
00:17:52,446 --> 00:17:53,781
[breathes uneasily]

286
00:17:55,533 --> 00:17:57,785
[Light] Damn it. After all that,
he got away?

287
00:17:58,369 --> 00:18:00,496
That's why you should have
just killed him.

288
00:18:01,205 --> 00:18:02,582
[wind blowing]

289
00:18:09,046 --> 00:18:10,798
[monitor beeps]

290
00:18:11,882 --> 00:18:15,970
[Light] Come on, please, Dad.
You can't die on me like this.

291
00:18:18,764 --> 00:18:19,640
Light...

292
00:18:20,057 --> 00:18:20,933
Yeah, Dad?

293
00:18:22,226 --> 00:18:23,311
I...

294
00:18:25,479 --> 00:18:27,398
My goodness...

295
00:18:27,898 --> 00:18:29,609
[whimpering]

296
00:18:29,900 --> 00:18:31,777
You'll be fine. It's okay.

297
00:18:33,446 --> 00:18:34,488
Light...

298
00:18:36,282 --> 00:18:41,078
I still have them.
I still have the Shinigami eyes.

299
00:18:42,204 --> 00:18:45,666
According to that Shinigami, Ryuk,

300
00:18:45,791 --> 00:18:49,337
I can't see the lifespan of someone
who owns a notebook.

301
00:18:49,503 --> 00:18:52,506
But I can see the numbers above your head.

302
00:18:53,633 --> 00:18:54,675
Light...

303
00:18:56,427 --> 00:18:58,262
You really aren't Kira.

304
00:18:59,722 --> 00:19:03,267
I'm so glad.
My son...

305
00:19:04,060 --> 00:19:06,354
Don't tell me
you're still worried about that, Chief.

306
00:19:06,604 --> 00:19:07,980
Of course he's not Kira.

307
00:19:08,689 --> 00:19:11,192
Come on, you shouldn't talk so much, Dad.

308
00:19:11,817 --> 00:19:14,987
That's important, but I've got
bigger things to deal with right now.

309
00:19:15,154 --> 00:19:17,657
I've got to get him
to write Mello's name in the notebook.

310
00:19:18,908 --> 00:19:21,952
I'm so sorry, but...

311
00:19:23,120 --> 00:19:28,000
In the end, I couldn't do it.
I couldn't bring myself to kill him.

312
00:19:28,668 --> 00:19:31,253
[Light] I can't just come out and say,
"It's not too late."

313
00:19:31,462 --> 00:19:34,674
No wait, maybe I can.
It all depends on how I do it.

314
00:19:35,049 --> 00:19:37,760
No one will think it's weird
if I get upset and panic.

315
00:19:39,595 --> 00:19:41,514
Come on, Dad, write his name!

316
00:19:41,931 --> 00:19:44,725
You can't let him beat you like this.
Write his name, Dad.

317
00:19:45,101 --> 00:19:48,562
With your last bit of strength!
Do you want to die in vain?

318
00:19:51,065 --> 00:19:52,066
D-- Dad, no!

319
00:19:54,193 --> 00:19:55,820
[Yagami, softly] Light...

320
00:20:05,204 --> 00:20:07,081
[monitor beeping goes flat]

321
00:20:10,209 --> 00:20:11,669
I'm sorry for your loss.

322
00:20:12,420 --> 00:20:13,337
Dad!

323
00:20:14,088 --> 00:20:15,047
Wake up!

324
00:20:15,548 --> 00:20:16,757
[yelling] Come on, damn it!

325
00:20:17,299 --> 00:20:22,012
Don't you die on me, you idiot!
Dad!

326
00:20:22,680 --> 00:20:23,848
[sobs]

327
00:20:48,038 --> 00:20:51,625
You're the Shinigami who came here
to take back this notebook, aren't you?

328
00:20:52,918 --> 00:20:54,420
[Sidoh] Yes.

329
00:20:54,545 --> 00:20:57,423
[Light] The notebook might be helpful
to the Kira investigation

330
00:20:57,631 --> 00:20:59,341
but we really only need one of them.

331
00:21:00,009 --> 00:21:01,343
I'll give this one back to you.

332
00:21:10,144 --> 00:21:14,815
[Sidoh] Humans who use the notebook
are cursed with fear, pain and misery. Hm.

333
00:21:15,322 --> 00:21:18,194
Of course,
Soichiro didn't use the notebook.

334
00:21:18,652 --> 00:21:21,614
He got to die believing
his son wasn't Kira.

335
00:21:22,239 --> 00:21:23,324
I guess that means...

336
00:21:24,116 --> 00:21:25,242
he was happy.

337
00:21:26,410 --> 00:21:33,334
TO BE CONTINUED
